  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Call to Repentance'
      title: A Call to Repentance
      number: 1
      content: '  In the eighth month of the second year [of the reign] of Darius
        [the king of Persia], the word of the Lord came to Zechariah (the Lord remembers)
        the son of Berechiah, the son of Iddo, the prophet, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThe Lord was extremely angry with your fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Therefore say to the Jews, \u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts (armies),
        \u201CReturn to Me,\u201D declares the Lord of hosts, \u201Cand I shall return
        to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Do not be like your fathers, to whom the former prophets proclaimed,
        \u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts, \u201CRepent [that is, change your way
        of thinking] and return now from your evil way [of life] and from your evil
        deeds.\u201D\u2009\u2019 But they did not listen or pay attention to Me,\u201D
        declares the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CYour fathers, where are they? And the prophets, do they live
        forever? "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Patrol of the Earth'
      title: Patrol of the Earth
      number: 6
      content: "But did not My words (warnings) and My statutes, which I commanded
        My servants the prophets, overtake your fathers? Then they repented and said,
        \u2018As the Lord of hosts planned to do to us [in discipline and punishment],
        in accordance with our ways and our deeds, so has He dealt with us.\u2019\u2009\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'On the twenty-fourth day of the eleventh month (Feb 15, 519 b.c.),
        which is the month of Shebat, in the second year of [the reign of] Darius,
        the word of the Lord came to Zechariah the prophet, the son of Berechiah,
        the son of Iddo, as follows: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the night I saw [a vision] and behold, a Man was riding on a red
        horse, and it stood among the myrtle trees that were in the ravine; and behind
        Him were horses: red, sorrel (reddish-brown), and white. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then I said, \u201CO my lord, what are these?\u201D And the angel
        who was speaking with me said, \u201CI will show you what these are.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the Man who stood among the myrtle trees answered and said, \u201CThese
        are the ones whom the Lord has sent to go throughout the earth and patrol
        it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the men on the horses answered the Angel of the Lord who stood
        among the myrtle trees and said, \u201CWe have gone throughout the earth
        [patrolling it] and behold, all the earth sits at rest [in peace and free
        from war].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the Angel of the Lord said, \u201CO Lord of hosts, how long
        will You withhold mercy and compassion from Jerusalem and the cities of Judah,
        against which You have had indignation and anger these seventy years [of
        the Babylonian captivity]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the Lord answered the angel who was speaking with me with gracious
        and comforting words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So the angel who was speaking with me said to me, \u201CProclaim,
        \u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts, \u201CI am jealous [with a burning, fiery
        passion] for Jerusalem and for Zion [demanding what is rightfully and uniquely
        mine] with a great jealousy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "But I am very angry with the nations who are at ease and feel secure;
        for while I was only a little angry, they furthered the disaster [against
        the people of Israel].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore, thus says the Lord, \u201CI have returned to Jerusalem
        with mercy and compassion. My house shall be built in it,\u201D says the
        Lord of hosts, \u201Cand a measuring line shall be stretched out over Jerusalem.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Proclaim again, \u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts, \u201CMy cities
        shall again overflow with prosperity, and the Lord shall again comfort Zion
        and again choose Jerusalem.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then I looked up, and saw four horns (powers)! '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So I asked the angel who was speaking with me, \u201CWhat are these?\u201D
        And he answered me, \u201CThese are the horns [the powerful Gentile nations]
        that have scattered Judah (the Southern Kingdom), Israel (the Northern Kingdom),
        and Jerusalem (capital city of Judah).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then the Lord showed me four craftsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I asked, \u201CWhat are these [horns and craftsmen] coming to do?\u201D
        And he said, \u201CThese are the horns (powers) that have scattered Judah
        so that no man raised up his head [because of the suffering inflicted by
        the Gentile nations]. But these craftsmen have come to terrify them and make
        them panic, and throw down the horns of the nations who have lifted up their
        horns against the land of Judah in order to scatter it.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Favor to Zion"
      title: "God\u2019s Favor to Zion"
      number: 1
      content: '  And I looked up, and saw a man with a measuring line in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So I said, \u201CWhere are you going?\u201D And he said to me, \u201CTo
        measure Jerusalem, to see how wide it is and how long it is.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And behold, the angel who was speaking with me was going out, and
        another angel was coming out to meet him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and he said to the second angel, \u201CRun, speak to that young man,
        saying, \u2018Jerusalem will be inhabited [like villages] without walls [spreading
        out into the open country] because of the great number of people and livestock
        in it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For I,\u2019 declares the Lord, \u2018will be a wall of fire around
        her [protecting her from enemies], and I will be the glory in her midst.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CHear this! Flee from [Babylon] the land of the north [which
        shall come under judgment],\u201D declares the Lord, \u201Cfor I have scattered
        you like the four winds of the heavens,\u201D declares the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CHear, Zion (Jerusalem)! Escape, you who are living with the
        daughter of Babylon!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For thus says the Lord of hosts, \u201CAfter glory He has sent Me
        against the nations which plunder you\u2014for he who touches you, touches
        the apple of His eye. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Behold, I will wave my hand over them and they shall become plunder
        for their own slaves. Then you shall know (recognize, understand fully) that
        the Lord of hosts has sent Me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Sing for joy and rejoice, O Daughter of Zion; for behold, I am coming,
        and I will dwell in your midst,\u201D declares the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CMany nations shall join themselves to the Lord in that day
        and shall be My people. And I will dwell in your midst, and you shall know
        (recognize, understand fully) that the Lord of hosts has sent Me to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The Lord will take possession of Judah as His portion in the holy
        land and will again choose Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBe still before the Lord, all mankind; for He is roused (raised
        up) from His holy habitation [in response to His persecuted people].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joshua, the High Priest'
      title: Joshua, the High Priest
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the guiding angel showed me Joshua the high priest [representing
        disobedient, sinful Israel] standing before the Angel of the Lord, and Satan
        standing at Joshua\u2019s right hand to be his adversary and to accuse him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Lord said to Satan, \u201CThe Lord rebuke you, Satan! Even
        the Lord, who [now and ever] has chosen Jerusalem, rebuke you! Is this not
        a log snatched and rescued from the fire?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Joshua was clothed with filthy (nauseatingly vile) garments and
        was standing before the Angel [of the Lord]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He spoke to those who stood before Him, saying, \u201CRemove the
        filthy garments from him.\u201D And He said to Joshua, \u201CSee, I have
        caused your wickedness to be taken away from you, and I will clothe and beautify
        you with rich robes [of forgiveness].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I (Zechariah) said, \u201CLet them put a clean turban on his
        head.\u201D So they put a clean turban on his head and clothed him with [rich]
        garments. And the Angel of the Lord stood by.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the Angel of the Lord [solemnly and earnestly] admonished Joshua,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Branch'
      title: The Branch
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, \u2018If you will walk in My ways
        [that is, remain faithful] and perform My service, then you will also govern
        My house and have charge of My courts, and I will give you free access [to
        My presence] among these who are standing here.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now listen, Joshua, the high priest, you and your colleagues who
        are sitting in front of you\u2014indeed they are men who are a symbol [of
        what is to come]\u2014for behold, I am going to bring in My servant the Branch
        [in Messianic glory]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For behold, the stone which I have set before Joshua; on that one
        stone are seven eyes (symbolizing infinite intelligence, omniscience). Behold,
        I will engrave an inscription on it,\u2019 declares the Lord of hosts, \u2018and
        I will remove the wickedness and guilt of this land in a single day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "In that day,\u2019 declares the Lord of hosts, \u2018every one of
        you will invite his neighbor to sit under his vine and his fig tree [enjoying
        peace and prosperity in the kingdom].\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Golden Lampstand and Olive Trees'
      title: The Golden Lampstand and Olive Trees
      number: 1
      content: '  And the angel who was speaking with me came back and awakened me,
        like a man who is awakened out of his sleep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He said to me, \u201CWhat do you see?\u201D I said, \u201CI see,
        and behold, a lampstand all of gold, with its bowl [for oil] on the top of
        it and its seven lamps on it with seven spouts belonging to each of the lamps
        which are on the top of it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And there are two olive trees by it, one on the right side of the
        bowl and the other on its left side [supplying it continuously with oil].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So I asked the angel who was speaking with me, \u201CWhat are these,
        my lord?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the angel who was speaking with me answered me, \u201CDo you
        not know what these are?\u201D And I said, \u201CNo, my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then he said to me, \u201CThis [continuous supply of oil] is the
        word of the Lord to Zerubbabel [prince of Judah], saying, \u2018Not by might,
        nor by power, but by My Spirit [of whom the oil is a symbol],\u2019 says
        the Lord of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018What are you, O great mountain [of obstacles]? Before Zerubbabel
        [who will rebuild the temple] you will become a plain (insignificant)! And
        he will bring out the capstone [of the new temple] with loud shouts of \u201CGrace,
        grace to it!\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Also the word of the Lord came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThe hands of Zerubbabel have laid the foundations of this house,
        and his hands will finish it. Then you will know (recognize, understand fully)
        that the Lord of hosts has sent me [as His messenger] to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Who [with reason] despises the day of small things (beginnings)?
        For these seven [eyes] shall rejoice when they see the plumb line in the
        hand of Zerubbabel. They are the eyes of the Lord which roam throughout the
        earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then I said to him [who was speaking with me], \u201CWhat are these
        two olive trees on the right side of the lampstand and on its left?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And a second time I said to him, \u201CWhat are these two olive branches
        which are beside the two golden pipes by which the golden oil is emptied?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he answered me, \u201CDo you not know what these are?\u201D And
        I said, \u201CNo, my lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he said, \u201CThese are the two sons of fresh oil [Joshua the
        high priest and Zerubbabel the prince of Judah] who are standing by the Lord
        of the whole earth [as His anointed ones].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Flying Scroll'
      title: The Flying Scroll
      number: 1
      content: '  Again I looked up, and I saw a scroll flying in the air!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the angel said to me, \u201CWhat do you see?\u201D And I answered,
        \u201CI see a flying scroll; its length is twenty cubits (thirty feet) and
        its width is ten cubits (fifteen feet).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then he said to me, \u201CThis is the curse that is going out over
        the face of the whole land; for everyone who steals will be cut off according
        to the writing on one side, and everyone who swears [oaths falsely] shall
        be cut off according to the writing on the other side. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I will send the curse out,\u201D declares the Lord of hosts, \u201Cand
        it will enter the house of the thief and the house of the one who swears
        falsely by My name; and it will spend the night in that house and consume
        it, both its timber and its stones.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the angel who was speaking with me came forward and said to
        me, \u201CNow look up and see what this is going forth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And I said, \u201CWhat is it?\u201D And he said, \u201CThis is the
        ephah (grain basket) going forth. This,\u201D he continued, \u201Cis their
        appearance throughout the land "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "(and behold, a [round, flat] lead cover was lifted up); and there
        sat a woman inside the ephah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then he said, \u201CThis is Wickedness (Godlessness)!\u201D And he
        threw her back down into the middle of the ephah and threw the lead cover
        on its opening. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then I looked up, and there were two women coming out with the wind
        in their wings; and they had wings like the wings of a stork, and they lifted
        up the ephah between the earth and the heavens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I said to the angel who was speaking with me, \u201CWhere are they
        taking the ephah?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And he said to me, \u201CTo the land of Shinar (Babylon) to build
        a temple for her; and when it is prepared, she shall be set there on her
        own pedestal.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Four Chariots'
      title: The Four Chariots
      number: 1
      content: '  Now again I looked up, and four chariots were coming out from between
        two mountains; and the mountains were mountains of [firm, immovable] bronze
        (divine judgment). '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The first chariot had red horses (war, bloodshed), the second chariot
        had black horses (famine, death), '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'the third chariot had white horses (victory), and the fourth chariot
        had strong dappled horses (death through judgment). '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then I said to the angel who was speaking with me, \u201CWhat are
        these, my lord?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The angel answered me, \u201CThese are the four spirits of the heavens,
        which go out after presenting themselves before the Lord of all the earth, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "with the chariot with the black horses going toward the north country;
        then the one with the white horses follows after them [because there are
        two northern powers to overcome], and the chariot with the dappled horses
        goes toward the south country.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When the strong horses went out, they were eager to patrol the earth.
        And the Lord said, \u201CGo, patrol the earth.\u201D So they patrolled the
        earth [watching and protecting it]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then He called out to me and said to me, \u201CSee, those who are
        going to the north country have quieted My Spirit [of wrath] in the north
        country.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The word of the Lord also came to me, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Symbolic Crowns'
      title: The Symbolic Crowns
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CTake an offering from the exiles, from Heldai, from Tobijah,
        and from Jedaiah [as representatives]; and you go the same day and enter
        the house of Josiah the son of Zephaniah, where they have arrived from Babylon.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Take silver and gold [from them], and make an ornate crown and set
        it on the head of Joshua the son of Jehozadak, the high priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then say to Joshua, \u2018Thus says the Lord of hosts, \u201CBehold
        (look, keep in sight, watch), a Man (Messiah) whose name is Branch, for He
        shall branch out from His place (Israel, the Davidic line); and He shall
        build the [ultimate] temple of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yes, [you are to build a temple of the Lord, but] it is He who shall
        build the [ultimate] temple of the Lord, and He shall bear the honor and
        majesty [as the only begotten of the Father] and sit and rule on His throne.
        And He shall be a Priest on His throne, and the counsel of peace shall be
        between the two offices [Priest and King].\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now the crown shall become a reminder in the temple of the Lord to
        Helem, Tobijah, Jedaiah, and Hen the son of Zephaniah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And those who are far away will come and [help] build the temple
        of the Lord.\u201D Then you shall know [without any doubt] that the Lord
        of hosts sent me (Zechariah) to you. And it will come about if you will diligently
        obey the [voice of the] Lord your God."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hearts like Flint'
      title: Hearts like Flint
      number: 1
      content: '  In the fourth year of [the reign of] King Darius [of Persia], the
        word of the Lord came to Zechariah on the fourth day of the ninth month,
        which is Chislev (Dec 7, 518 b.c.). '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now the people of Bethel had sent Sharezer and Regem-melech and their
        men to seek the favor of the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "speaking to the priests who belong to the house of the Lord of hosts
        and to the prophets, saying, \u201C[Now that I am returned from exile] shall
        I weep in the fifth month [mourning the destruction of the temple], and fast
        as I have done these many years [in Babylon]?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord of hosts came to me (Zechariah), saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CSpeak to all the people of the land and to the priests, saying,
        \u2018When you fasted and mourned in the fifth and seventh months these seventy
        years [that you were in exile], was it actually for Me that you fasted? "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When you eat and when you drink, do you not eat for yourselves and
        do you not drink for yourselves [to satisfy your own needs]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Should you not hear the words which the Lord proclaimed by the former
        prophets, when Jerusalem was inhabited and prosperous along with her cities
        around her, and the South (the Negev) and the foothills were inhabited?\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to Zechariah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThus has the Lord of hosts said, \u2018Dispense true justice
        and practice kindness and compassion, to each other; "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and do not oppress or exploit the widow or the fatherless, the stranger
        or the poor; and do not devise or even imagine evil in your hearts against
        one another.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But they refused to listen and pay attention and turned a stubborn
        shoulder [stiffening themselves in resistance] and stopped up their ears. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They made their hearts [hard] like flint, so that they could not
        hear the law and the words which the Lord of hosts had sent by His Spirit
        through the former prophets. Therefore great wrath came from the Lord of
        hosts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And just as He called and they would not listen, so they called and
        I would not listen,\u201D says the Lord of hosts; "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201Cbut I scattered them with a storm wind among all the nations
        whom they have not known. Thus the land was desolate after they had gone,
        so that no one passed through or returned, for they [by their sins] had made
        the pleasant land desolate and deserted.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Coming Peace and Prosperity of Zion'
      title: The Coming Peace and Prosperity of Zion
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the word of the Lord of hosts came [to me], saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, \u2018I am jealous for Zion with
        great jealousy [demanding what is rightfully and uniquely mine], and I am
        jealous for her with great wrath [against her enemies].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Thus says the Lord, \u2018I shall return to Zion and will dwell in
        the midst of Jerusalem, and Jerusalem shall be called the [faithful] City
        of Truth, and the mountain of the Lord of hosts will be called the Holy Mountain.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts, \u2018Old men and old women will again
        sit in the streets (public places) of Jerusalem, each man with his staff
        in his hand because of his advanced age. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the streets of the city will be filled with boys and girls playing
        in its streets.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts, \u2018If it is difficult in the eyes
        of the remnant of this people in those days [in which this comes to pass],
        will it also be difficult in My sight?\u2019 declares the Lord of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts, \u2018Behold, I am going to save My
        people from the east country and from the west, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and I will bring them home and they will live in the midst of Jerusalem;
        and they shall be My people, and I will be their God in truth (faithfulness)
        and in righteousness.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, \u2018Let your hands be strong,
        you who in these days hear these words from the mouths of the prophets who,
        on the day that the foundation of the house of the Lord of hosts was laid,
        foretold that the temple might be rebuilt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For before those days there were no wages for man or animal; nor
        was there any peace or success for him who went out or came in because of
        his enemies, for I set all men against one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But now [in this time since you began to build] I will not treat
        the remnant of this people as in the former days,\u2019 declares the Lord
        of hosts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u2018For there the seed will produce peace and prosperity; the vine
        will yield its fruit, and the ground will produce its increase, and the heavens
        will give their dew. And I will cause the remnant of this people to inherit
        and possess all these things. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And as you have been a curse among the nations, O house of Judah
        (Southern Kingdom) and house of Israel (Northern Kingdom), so I will save
        you, that you may be a blessing. Fear not; let your hands be strong.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CFor thus says the Lord of hosts, \u2018Just as I planned to
        do harm to you when your fathers provoked Me to wrath,\u2019 says the Lord
        of hosts, \u2018and I did not relent, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'so I have again planned in these days to do good to Jerusalem and
        to the house of Judah. Do not fear! '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'These are the things which you should do: speak the truth with one
        another; judge with truth and pronounce the judgment that brings peace in
        [the courts at] your gates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And let none of you devise or even imagine evil in your heart against
        another, and do not love lying or half-truths; for all these things I hate,\u2019
        declares the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord of hosts came to me (Zechariah), saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, \u2018The fast of the fourth [month
        to mourn the breaching of Jerusalem\u2019s walls], the fast of the fifth
        [month to mourn the temple\u2019s destruction], the fast of the seventh [month
        to mourn Gedaliah\u2019s assassination], and the fast of the tenth [month
        to mourn the siege of Jerusalem] will become times of joy and gladness and
        cheerful feasts for the house of Judah; so [to bring this about] love truth
        and peace.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord of hosts, \u2018It will come to pass that
        peoples and the inhabitants of many cities will come [to Jerusalem]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The inhabitants of one [city] will go to another, saying, \u201CLet
        us go at once to ask the favor of the Lord and to seek the Lord of hosts.
        I will go also.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So many peoples and powerful nations will come to seek the Lord of
        hosts in Jerusalem and to ask the Lord for His favor.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Thus says the Lord of hosts, \u2018In those days ten men [as representatives]
        from all the nations will grasp the robe of a Jew, saying, \u201CLet us go
        with you, for we have heard that God is with you.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prophecies against Neighboring Nations'
      title: Prophecies against Neighboring Nations
      number: 1
      content: '  The oracle (a burdensome message) of the word of the Lord is against
        the land of Hadrach [in Syria], with Damascus as its resting place (for the
        eyes of men, especially of all the tribes of Israel, are toward the Lord),  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Hamath also, which borders on it (Damascus),Tyre and Sidon, though
        they are very wise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For Tyre built herself an [impregnable] stronghold [on an island
        offshore],And she has heaped up silver like dustAnd gold like the mire of
        the streets.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Behold, the Lord will dispossess herAnd throw her wealth into the
        sea;And Tyre will be devoured by fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Ashkelon will see it and fear;Gaza will writhe in pain,And Ekron,
        for her hope and expectation, has been ruined.The king will perish from Gaza,And
        Ashkelon will not be inhabited.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And a mongrel race will live in Ashdod,And I will put an end to the
        pride and arrogance of the Philistines.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will take the blood from their mouthsAnd their detestable things
        from between their teeth [those repulsive, idolatrous sacrifices eaten with
        the blood].Then they too will be a remnant for our God,And be like a clan
        in Judah,And Ekron will be like one of the Jebusites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then I will camp around My house [as a guard] because of an army,Because
        of him who passes by and returns;And no oppressor will again overrun them
        (Israel),For now My eyes are upon them [providentially protecting them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Rejoice greatly, O Daughter of Zion!Shout aloud, O Daughter of Jerusalem!Behold,
        your King (Messianic King) is coming to you;He is righteous and endowed with
        salvation,  Humble and unassuming [in submission to the will of the Father]
        and riding on a donkey,Upon a colt, the foal of a donkey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Salvation of Judah and Ephraim'
      title: Salvation of Judah and Ephraim
      number: 10
      content: 'I will cut off the [war] chariot from EphraimAnd the [war] horse
        from Jerusalem,And the bow of war will be cut off.And He will speak [words
        of] peace to the nations,And His dominion shall be from sea to sea [absolutely
        endless],And from the River [Euphrates] to the ends of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As for you also, because of the blood of My covenant with you [My
        chosen people, the covenant that was sealed with blood]I have freed your
        prisoners from the waterless pit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Return to the stronghold [of security and prosperity], O prisoners
        who have the hope;Even today I am declaring that I will restore double [your
        former prosperity] to you [as firstborn among nations].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For I will bend Judah as My bow,I will fit the bow with Ephraim [as
        My arrow].And I will stir up your sons, O Zion, against your sons, O Greece,And
        will make you [Israel] like the sword of a warrior.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the Lord will be seen [hovering] over them [protecting His people],And
        His arrow will go forth like lightning;And the Lord God will blow the trumpetAnd
        will march in the windstorms of the south.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The Lord of hosts shall defend and protect them;And they will devour
        [the enemy] and trample down the slingstones [that have missed their mark],And
        they will drink [of victory] and be boisterous as with wine;And they shall
        be filled like sacrificial bowls [used to catch the blood],  Drenched like
        the corners of the [sacrificial] altar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the Lord their God shall save them on that dayAs the flock of
        His people;For they are like the [precious] jewels of a crown,Displayed and
        glittering in His land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For how great is God\u2019s goodness and how great is His beauty!
        And how great [He will make Israel\u2019s] goodliness and [Israel\u2019s]
        beauty!Grain and new wine will make the young men and virgins flourish."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Will Bless Judah and Ephraim'
      title: God Will Bless Judah and Ephraim
      number: 1
      content: '  Ask for rain from the Lord at the time of the spring rain.It is
        the Lord who makes the thunder clouds;And He will give them showers of rain,
        grass in the field to everyone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the teraphim (household idols) speak wickedness (emptiness, worthlessness),And
        the diviners see lying visionsAnd tell false dreams;They comfort in vain.Therefore
        the people wander like sheep,They are afflicted and suffer because there
        is no shepherd.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CMy anger is kindled against the shepherds [who are not true
        shepherds],And I shall punish the male goats (leaders);For the Lord of hosts
        has visited His flock, the house of Judah (the Southern Kingdom),And will
        make them like His beautiful and majestic horse in the battle.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'From them (Judah) shall come the Cornerstone,From them the tent peg,From
        them the bow of battle,From them every ruler, all of them together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They will be like mighty menTrampling down their enemies in the mire
        of the streets in the battle;And they will fight because the Lord is with
        them,And the [enemies\u2019] riders on horses will be shamed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I will strengthen the house of Judah [making it superior],And I will
        save the house of Joseph.I will bring them back [and allow them to live securely],Because
        I have had compassion on them.They will be as though I had not rejected them,For
        I am the Lord their God, and I will listen and answer them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Ephraim will be like a mighty warrior,And their heart will rejoice
        as if from wine;Yes, their children will see it and rejoice;Their heart will
        rejoice and shout triumphantly in the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will whistle for them and gather them together,For I have redeemed
        them;And they will increase [again] as they have increased before [in Egypt].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When I scatter them among the nations,They will remember Me in far
        countries,And with their children they will live and come back [to Me and
        the land I gave them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I will bring them (all Israel) back home again from the land of EgyptAnd
        gather them from Assyria,And I will bring them into the land of Gilead and
        Lebanon [the land on the east and on the west of the Jordan]Until no room
        can be found for them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they will pass through the sea of distress and anxiety [with
        the Lord leading His people, as at the Red Sea]And He will strike the waves
        in the sea,So that all the depths of the Nile will dry up;And the pride of
        Assyria will be brought downAnd the scepter [of the taskmasters] of Egypt
        will pass away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And I will strengthen Israel in the Lord,And they will walk [and
        glory] in His name,\u201D declares the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Doomed Flock'
      title: The Doomed Flock
      number: 1
      content: '  Open your doors, O Lebanon,That fire may devour your cedars.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Wail, O cypress, for the cedar has fallen,Because the magnificent
        trees have been destroyed;Wail, O oaks of Bashan,For the inaccessible forest
        [on the steep mountainside] has come down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "There is a sound of the shepherds\u2019 wail,For their splendor (grazing
        land) is ruined;There is a sound of the young lions\u2019 roar,For the pride
        of the Jordan is ruined.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Thus says the Lord my God, \u201CPasture the flock doomed for slaughter, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "whose buyers slay them and go unpunished, and those who sell them
        say, \u2018Blessed be the Lord, for I have become rich!\u2019 And their own
        shepherds have no pity on them nor protect them [from the wolves]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For I will no longer have pity on the inhabitants of the land,\u201D
        declares the Lord; \u201Cbut behold, I will cause the men to fall, each into
        the hand of another and into the hands of his [foreign] king. And the enemy
        will strike the land, and I will not rescue the people from their hand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So I [Zechariah] pastured the flock doomed for slaughter, truly [as
        the name implies] the most miserable of sheep. And I took two [shepherd\u2019s]
        staffs, the one I called Favor (Grace) and the other I called Union (Bonds);
        so I pastured the flock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then I eliminated the three [incompetent, unfit] shepherds [the civil
        rulers, the priests, and the prophets] in one month, for I was impatient
        with them, and they also were tired of me and despised me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So I said, \u201CI will not pasture you. What is to die, let it die,
        and what is to be destroyed, let it be destroyed; and let the survivors devour
        one another\u2019s flesh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I took my staff, Favor, and broke it in pieces, breaking the covenant
        which I had made with all the peoples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So the covenant was broken on that day, and thus the most wretched
        of the flock who were watching me realized that it was the word of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I said to them, \u201CIf it seems good to you, give me my wages;
        but if not, do not.\u201D So they weighed out thirty pieces of silver as
        my wages. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u201CThrow it to the potter [as if to
        the dogs]\u2014that magnificent sum at which I am valued by them!\u201D So
        I took the thirty pieces of silver and threw them to the potter in the house
        of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then I broke my second staff, Union, into pieces to break the brotherhood
        between Judah (the Southern Kingdom) and Israel (the Northern Kingdom).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The Lord said to me, \u201CTake again for yourself the equipment
        [of a shepherd, but this time] of a foolish shepherd. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For behold, I am going to raise up a [false] shepherd in the land
        who will not care for the perishing, seek the scattered, heal the broken,
        or feed the healthy; but will eat the flesh of the fat ones and tear off
        their hoofs [to consume everything].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Woe (judgment is coming) to the worthless and foolish shepherdWho
        deserts the flock!The sword will strike his armAnd his right eye!His arm
        shall be totally witheredAnd his right eye completely blinded.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jerusalem to Be Attacked'
      title: Jerusalem to Be Attacked
      number: 1
      content: '  The oracle (a burdensome message) of the word of the Lord concerning
        Israel.  Thus declares the Lord who stretches out the heavens and lays the
        foundation of the earth and forms the spirit of man within him: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am going to make Jerusalem a cup that causes reeling
        (staggering) to all the surrounding peoples; and when the siege is against
        Jerusalem, it will also be against Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And in that day I will make Jerusalem a heavy stone for all the peoples;
        all who lift it will be severely injured. And all the nations of the earth
        will come and be gathered against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "In that day,\u201D declares the Lord, \u201CI will strike every horse
        with panic and his rider with madness; but I will open My eyes and watch
        over the house of Judah, and will strike every horse of the [opposing] nations
        with blindness. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the clans of Judah will say in their hearts, \u2018The inhabitants
        of Jerusalem are our strength in the Lord of hosts, their God.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIn that day I will make the clans of Judah like a firepot in
        a woodpile, and like a flaming torch among sheaves [of grain]. They will
        devour all the surrounding peoples on the right hand and on the left; and
        the people of Jerusalem will again live [securely] in their own place, in
        Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The Lord shall save the tents of Judah first, so that the glory of
        the house of David and the glory of the inhabitants of Jerusalem will not
        be magnified above Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In that day the Lord will defend the people of Jerusalem, and the
        one who is impaired among them in that day [of persecution] will become [strong
        and noble] like David; and the house of David will be like God, like the
        Angel of the Lord [who is] before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And in that day I will seek to destroy all the nations that come
        against Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CI will pour out on the house of David and on the people of
        Jerusalem, the Spirit of grace (unmerited favor) and supplication. And they
        will look at Me whom they have pierced; and they will mourn for Him as one
        mourns for an only son, and they will weep bitterly over Him as one who weeps
        bitterly over a firstborn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'In that day there shall be a great mourning in Jerusalem, like the
        mourning of [the city of] Hadadrimmon in the Valley of Megiddo [over beloved
        King Josiah]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The land will mourn, every family by itself; the [royal] family of
        the house of David by itself and their wives by themselves; the family of
        the house of Nathan [David\u2019s son] by itself and their wives by themselves; "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the [priestly] family of the house of Levi by itself and their wives
        by themselves; the family of Shimei [grandson of Levi] by itself and their
        wives by themselves; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: all the families that remain, each by itself, and their wives by themselves
        [each with an overwhelming individual regret for having blindly rejected
        their Messiah].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: False Prophets Ashamed'
      title: False Prophets Ashamed
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIn that day a fountain shall be opened for the house of David
        and for the people of Jerusalem for [cleansing from] sin and impurity.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CIn that day,\u201D declares the Lord of hosts, \u201CI will
        cut off the names of the idols from the land, and they will no longer be
        remembered. I will also remove the [false] prophets and the unclean spirit
        from the land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And if anyone still [appears as a prophet and falsely] prophesies,
        then his father and his mother who gave birth to him will say to him, \u2018You
        shall not live, for you have spoken lies in the name of the Lord\u2019; and
        his father and his mother who gave birth to him shall pierce him through
        when he prophesies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And in that day the [false] prophets will each be ashamed of his
        vision when he prophesies, and they will not wear a hairy robe [of true prophets]
        in order to deceive, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "but he will [deny his identity and] say, \u2018I am no prophet. I
        work the ground, because a man sold me as a slave in my youth.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And one will say to him, \u2018What are these wounds between your
        arms?\u2019 Then he will answer, \u2018Those wounds I received in the house
        of my friends.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CAwake, O sword, against My Shepherd,And against the Man, My
        Associate,\u201DDeclares the Lord of hosts.\u201CStrike the Shepherd so that
        the sheep [of the flock] may be scattered;And I will turn My hand and stretch
        it out against the little ones [of the flock].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "It will come about in all the land,\u201DDeclares the Lord,\u201CTwo
        parts in it will be cut off and perish,But the third will be left alive.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And I will bring the third part through the fire,Refine them as silver
        is refined,And test them as gold is tested.They will call on My name,And
        I will listen and answer them;I will say, \u2018They are My people,\u2019And
        they will say, \u2018The Lord is my God.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God Will Battle Jerusalem\u2019s Foes"
      title: "God Will Battle Jerusalem\u2019s Foes"
      number: 1
      content: '  Behold, a day is coming for the Lord when the spoil taken from
        you (Jerusalem) will be divided in your midst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For I will gather all nations against Jerusalem to battle, and the
        city will be captured and the houses plundered and the women ravished; and
        half of the city will be exiled, but the rest of the people will not be cut
        off from the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the Lord will go forth and fight against those nations, as when
        He fights on a day of battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'In that day His feet shall stand on the Mount of Olives, which lies
        before Jerusalem on the east; and the Mount of Olives will be split in half
        from the east to the west by a very large valley, and half of the mountain
        will move toward the north and half of it toward the south. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You will flee by the valley of My mountains, for the valley of the
        mountains will reach to Azel; and you will flee just as you fled from the
        earthquake in the days of Uzziah king of Judah. Then the Lord my God will
        come, and all the holy ones (believers, angels) with Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In that day there will be no light; the glorious ones (heavenly bodies)
        shall be darkened. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But it will be a unique day which is known to the Lord\u2014not day
        and not night, but at evening time there will be light.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: God Will Be King over All'
      title: God Will Be King over All
      number: 8
      content: 'And in that day living waters will flow out from Jerusalem, half
        of them to the eastern sea (Dead Sea) and half of them to the western sea
        (the Mediterranean); it will be in summer as well as in winter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the Lord shall be king over all the earth; in that day the Lord
        shall be the only one [worshiped], and His name the only one.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "All the land will be changed into a plain from Geba to Rimmon, [the
        Rimmon that is] south of Jerusalem; but Jerusalem will rise and remain [lifted
        up] on its site from Benjamin\u2019s Gate to the place of the First Gate
        to the Corner Gate, and from the Tower of Hananel to the king\u2019s wine
        presses. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'It will be inhabited, for there will no longer be a curse, for Jerusalem
        will dwell in security.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now this will be the plague with which the Lord shall strike all
        the peoples that have warred against Jerusalem: Their flesh will rot while
        they stand on their feet, and their eyes will rot in their sockets, and their
        tongue will rot in their mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "In that day a great panic and dismay from the Lord will fall on them;
        and they will seize one another\u2019s hand, and the hand of the one will
        be raised against the hand of the other. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Judah also will fight at Jerusalem; and the wealth of all the surrounding
        nations will be gathered together\u2014gold and silver and garments in great
        abundance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So like this plague [on men] there will be the plague on the horses,
        mules, camels, donkeys, and all the livestock in those camps.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then everyone who is left of all the nations that went against Jerusalem
        will go up from year to year to worship the King, the Lord of hosts, and
        celebrate the Feast of Booths (Tabernacles). '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And it will be that whichever of the families of the earth does not
        go up to Jerusalem to worship the King, the Lord of hosts, there will be
        no rain on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'If the family of Egypt does not go up [to Jerusalem] and present
        themselves, then no rain will fall on them. It will be the plague with which
        the Lord will strike the nations who do not go up to celebrate the Feast
        of Booths (Tabernacles). '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'This will be the [consequent] punishment [for the sin] of Egypt,
        and the [consequent] punishment [for the sin] of all the nations that do
        not go up to celebrate the Feast of Booths (Tabernacles).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "In that day there will be written on the little bells on the horses,
        \u201CHOLY TO THE <span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">Lord</span>.\u201D
        And the cooking pots in the L<smallcaps>ord</smallcaps>\u2019s house will
        be [holy to the Lord] like the bowls before the altar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Every cooking pot in [all the houses in] Jerusalem and in Judah will
        be holy to the Lord of hosts, and all who sacrifice will come and take them
        and boil [their sacrifices] in them. And in that day there will no longer
        be a Canaanite [that is, any godless or spiritually unclean person, whether
        Jew or Gentile] in the house of the Lord of hosts.
      comments: []
